<br>
Because the mage mez spell Elemental Silence is 3 seconds long, while the Enchanter mez spell is 2.5, the mage spell is<br>
affected by FOCUS, thus making it a 1.6second cast,<br>
almost impossible to interrupt even when being beat on.<br>
<br>
Mages are greater than enchanters in mezzing and recharming elementals thus stepping on enchanters core abilities <br>
(o just like mages and charmed pets)<br>
<br>
<br>
Quote from another board:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/viewforum.php?f=9">forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/...um.php?f=9</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Elemental silence 3 sec cast mez, Call of the arch mage 5 sec charm. These were the 2 spells he was casting, and he does not have Channeling focus, or Combat Agility while I had at that time Cf 1 and lightning reflex 2. I was using a mag summoned spell haste item. <br>
<br>
His Pets DPS was between 700 to 800 and some how he was able to mes it every time during the 3 hours, by just standing toe to toe with it. I had more AA then him, better spells, more runes, and if my 350 dps pet resisted WOM I had to put some distance between us to let my spells gems refresh before I tried to mez or charm again. <br>
<br>
He only had 2 things more then me, hp's that was off set by my runes and over 300 more AC.&quot;<br>
&quot;He had 3 things on you. A mez with a 3 second casting time instead of 2.5. <br>
<br>
Naki's Superior Pernicity (effect of mage summoned ring): <br>
Limit: Min Casting Time(3.0 sec) <br>
<br>
Blessing of Reverence: <br>
Limit: Min Casting Time(3.0 sec) <br>
<br>
Affliction Haste IV: <br>
Limit: Min Casting Time(3.0 sec) <br>
<br>
Thanks to bad design, because his spell has a 3 second casting time, it's faster casting than your 2.5 time, as low as 1.6 seconds with Affliction Haste IV + Blessings of Reverence. The limit should have been a min casting time you can reduce it to, not a min effect at which the effect works. <br>
<br>
Stupid design we really should try and encourage Verant to fix.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's ironic that by giving a spell a longer cast time to keep it from being better than another, they actually do the opposite by putting it within focus item parameters. <br>
<br>
I'd agree, it's probably an oversite and probably the main reason the Mage was able to do it better than you. That said, they can only really use the spell in like 2 zones in PoP before Teir 3, so it's not something I'd go on a rampage about them fixing (like a Mage would if the situation was reversed...)&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You War on Chanter abilities,<br>
then the War will come to you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Everyone should SHUT UP and play their class they<br>
chose and stop nerfing each other.<br>
<br>
