<br>
A week ago I was on the west castle wall in PoV. A shaman friend of mine and myself had died due to a golem add. These mobs just do so much damage that even when slowed they can kill the average player in a few rounds. We came back to get our corpses, and a enchanter had move into the camp we had solo. I stayed for about 40mins to watch her, and I was truly amazed. She was charming the golems, chain pulling, mezzing two at a time then debuffing them and let pet have at them. She said she could make about 1aa every 15-20mins. I asked her how often she would die and she said around two times per session but then followed it up to say that it wasn't a big deal because she was lvl 65, and two deaths isn't a issue because there is always a cleric around to rez, and two deaths in level 65 is worth the 5 to 8 aa she makes in less then 2hours of soloing. /boggle<br>
<br>
Yes I am pissed that I can no longer solo with most of the tools I was able to solo with pre-60. Yes I am jealous of the fact that a &quot;group class&quot;, can out damage me whenever they feel like it, and completely, and utterly blows away my solo ability, while being able to get a group with one shout of &quot;lvl 65 enchanter LFG&quot;. That doesn't seem fair or balanced. Enchanters should not be able to out damage three rogues with one spell, and a few buffs when they are not even a damage class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pissed1vi2soe@themagicianstower>Pissed1VI2SOE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 534<br> <font color=#333333>(1/7/03 8:47:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Waste of time</span><hr size=1> hmmmmmmmm<br>
